PortList.name: PortList
PortList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

VlanIndex.name: VlanIndex
VlanIndex.description: A value used to index per-VLAN tables: values of 0 and 4095 are not permitted; if the value is between 1 and 4094 inclusive, it represents an IEEE 802.1Q VLAN-ID with global scope within a given bridged domain (see VlanId textual convention). If the value is greater than 4095 then it represents a VLAN with scope local to the particular agent, i.e. one without a global VLAN-ID assigned to it. Such VLANs are outside the scope of IEEE 802.1Q but it is convenient to be able to manage them in the same way using this MIB.

InterfaceIndex.name: InterfaceIndex
InterfaceIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface or interface sub-layer in the managed system. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

DropDirection.name: DropDirection
DropDirection.description: Representing the direction of dropping packets, if applicable.

hh3cifXXTable.name: hh3cifXXTable
hh3cifXXTable.description: Extended H3C private interface information table.

hh3cifXXEntry.name: hh3cifXXEntry
hh3cifXXEntry.description: Entries of extended H3C private interface information table.

hh3cifUnBoundPort.name: hh3cifUnBoundPort
hh3cifUnBoundPort.description: Whether it is the unbound port. (true indicates that the port is the main port of the aggregation or the port does not participate in the aggregation.)

hh3cifISPhyPort.name: hh3cifISPhyPort
hh3cifISPhyPort.description: Whether it is a physical interface.

hh3cifAggregatePort.name: hh3cifAggregatePort
hh3cifAggregatePort.description: Whether it is the aggregated port. (if the port participates in the aggregation, this value is true.)

hh3cifMirrorPort.name: hh3cifMirrorPort
hh3cifMirrorPort.description: Whether it is a mirror port.

hh3cifVLANType.name: hh3cifVLANType
hh3cifVLANType.description: port vlan types. hybrid (3) port can carry multiple VLANs. If fabric function is supported, fabric(4) means the port is a fabric port.

hh3cifMcastControl.name: hh3cifMcastControl
hh3cifMcastControl.description: Broadcast storm suppression with the step length of 1, ranging from 1 to 100 percent. In some products the step is 5, ranging from 5 to 100.

hh3cifSrcMacControl.name: hh3cifSrcMacControl
hh3cifSrcMacControl.description: Whether to filter by source MAC address.

hh3cifClearStat.name: hh3cifClearStat
hh3cifClearStat.description: Clear all port statistics. Read operation not supported.

hh3cifXXBasePortIndex.name: hh3cifXXBasePortIndex
hh3cifXXBasePortIndex.description: Index number of the port and the first port index of the device is 1.

hh3cifPpsMcastControl.name: hh3cifPpsMcastControl
hh3cifPpsMcastControl.description: The broadcast suppression with pps(packet per second) type. The max value is determined by the port type and product.

hh3cifPpsBcastDisValControl.name: hh3cifPpsBcastDisValControl
hh3cifPpsBcastDisValControl.description: Control the port's pps(packet per second) broadcast suppression. When the port is enabled, its pps broadcast suppression value is the global disperse value, and when disabled, it doesn't suppress broadcast.

hh3cifUniSuppressionStep.name: hh3cifUniSuppressionStep
hh3cifUniSuppressionStep.description: The step of unicast suppression in ratio mode.

hh3cifPpsUniSuppressionMax.name: hh3cifPpsUniSuppressionMax
hh3cifPpsUniSuppressionMax.description: The max pps(packet per second) value of unicast suppression in pps mode.

hh3cifMulSuppressionStep.name: hh3cifMulSuppressionStep
hh3cifMulSuppressionStep.description: The step of multicast suppression in ratio mode.

hh3cifPpsMulSuppressionMax.name: hh3cifPpsMulSuppressionMax
hh3cifPpsMulSuppressionMax.description: The max pps(packet per second) value of multicast suppression in pps mode.

hh3cifUniSuppression.name: hh3cifUniSuppression
hh3cifUniSuppression.description: The unicast suppression with the ranging from 1 to 100 percent in ratio mode. The step is determined by hh3cifUniSuppressionStep.

hh3cifPpsUniSuppression.name: hh3cifPpsUniSuppression
hh3cifPpsUniSuppression.description: The unicast suppression in pps(packet per second) mode. The max value is determined by hh3cifPpsUniSuppressionMax.

hh3cifMulSuppression.name: hh3cifMulSuppression
hh3cifMulSuppression.description: The multicast suppression with ranging from 1 to 100 percent in ratio mode. The step is determined by hh3cifMulSuppressionStep.

hh3cifPpsMulSuppression.name: hh3cifPpsMulSuppression
hh3cifPpsMulSuppression.description: The multicast suppression in pps(packet per second) mode. The max pps value is determined by hh3cifPpsMulSuppressionMax.

hh3cifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax.name: hh3cifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax
hh3cifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the multicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Mbps) that a port can be configured.

hh3cifBMbpsMulSuppression.name: hh3cifBMbpsMulSuppression
hh3cifBMbpsMulSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based multicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Mbps. The upper limit of the multicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Mbps) is the value of hh3cifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax in the entry. The default value of hh3cifBMbpsMulSuppression is the value of hh3cifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax.

hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax.name: hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax
hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the multicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Kbps) that a port can be configured.

hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep.name: hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep
hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep.description: The step of multicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Kbps).

hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppression.name: hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppression
hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based multicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Kbps. The upper limit of the multicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Kbps) is the value of hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax in the entry. The value of hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppression must be multiple of the value of hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep. The default value of hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppression is the value of hh3cifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax.

hh3cifUnknownPacketDropMul.name: hh3cifUnknownPacketDropMul
hh3cifUnknownPacketDropMul.description: Control the port's unknown-multicast packets drop. When inbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-multicast packets in inbound direction. When outbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-multicast packets in outbound direction. When both directions are enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-multicast packets in both inbound and outbound directions.

hh3cifUnknownPacketDropUni.name: hh3cifUnknownPacketDropUni
hh3cifUnknownPacketDropUni.description: Control the port's unknown-unicast packets drop. When inbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-unicast packets in inbound direction. When outbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-unicast packets in outbound direction. When both directions are enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-unicast packets in both inbound and outbound directions.

hh3cifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax.name: hh3cifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax
hh3cifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the unicast suppression with bandwidth-based (Mbps) that a port can be configured.

hh3cifBMbpsUniSuppression.name: hh3cifBMbpsUniSuppression
hh3cifBMbpsUniSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based Unicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Mbps. The upper limit of the unicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Mbps) is the value of hh3cifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax in the entry. The default value of hh3cifBMbpsUniSuppression is the value of hh3cifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax.

hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax.name: hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax
hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the unicast suppression with bandwidth-based (Kbps) that a port can be configured.

hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep.name: hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep
hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep.description: The step of unicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Kbps).

hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppression.name: hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppression
hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based unicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Kbps. The upper limit of the unicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Kbps) is the value of hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax in the entry. The value of hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppression must be multiple of the value of hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep. The default value of hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppression is the value of hh3cifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax.

hh3cifAggregateModel.description: Load sharing mode for the port aggregation.

hh3cifAggregateOperStatus.name: hh3cifAggregateOperStatus

hh3cifHybridTaggedVlanListLow.name: hh3cifHybridTaggedVlanListLow
hh3cifHybridTaggedVlanListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. hh3cifComboPortIndex.name: hh3cifComboPortIndex
hh3cifComboPortIndex.description: The combo-port interface index. Its value is the same as the value of ifIndex in ifTable, but only includes indexes of the combo-port interfaces.

hh3cifComboPortCurActive.name: hh3cifComboPortCurActive
hh3cifComboPortCurActive.description: Current active interface of combo interfaces. The value 'fiber' means the interface with fiber connector of the pair of combo-port interfaces is active. The value 'copper' means the interface with copper connector of the pair is active. The value 'na' means not supported.

hh3cSwitchPortMax.name: hh3cSwitchPortMax

hh3cifVLANTrunkIndex.description: Index number of the VLANTrunk interface.

hh3cifVLANTrunkGvrpRegistration.name: hh3cifVLANTrunkGvrpRegistration
hh3cifVLANTrunkGvrpRegistration.description: GMOSAIC registration information normal: This is the default configuration. Allow create, register and unregister vlans dynamiclly at this port. fixed: Aallow create and register vlan manually at this port. Prevent from unregistering vlans or registering known vlans of this port at another trunk port. forbidden: Unregister all vlans but vlan 1, forbid to create or register any other vlans at this port.

hh3cifVLANTrunkPassListLow.name: hh3cifVLANTrunkPassListLow
hh3cifVLANTrunkPassListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each actually passed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is actually passed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not actually passed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hh3cifVLANTrunkPassListHigh.name: hh3cifVLANTrunkPassListHigh
hh3cifVLANTrunkPassListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. hh3cifVLANTrunkAllowListLow.name: hh3cifVLANTrunkAllowListLow
hh3cifVLANTrunkAllowListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each allowed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is allowed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not allowed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hh3cethernetEntry.name: hh3cethernetEntry
hh3cethernetEntry.description: Entries of Ethernet port attribute table

hh3cifEthernetMdi.name: hh3cifEthernetMdi
hh3cifEthernetMdi.description: Type of the line connected to the port. MDI-II (straight-through cable): 1 MDI-X (crossover cable): 2 MDI-AUTO (auto-sensing): 3

hh3cMaxMacLearn.name: hh3cMaxMacLearn
hh3cMaxMacLearn.description: The maximum number of MAC addresses that the port can learn. The value -1 means that the number of Mac addresses that the port can learn is unlimited.

hh3cifMacAddressLearn.name: hh3cifMacAddressLearn
hh3cifMacAddressLearn.description: This object indicates if the interface is allowed to learn mac address. eanbled(1) means the interface can learn mac address, otherwise disabled(2) can be set.

hh3cifEthernetTest.name: hh3cifEthernetTest
hh3cifEthernetTest.description: Test this interface. The actual testing will be different according to products. Read operation not supported.

hh3cifMacAddrLearnMode.name: hh3cifMacAddrLearnMode
hh3cifMacAddrLearnMode.description: Status indicates mac address learn mode of the interface. IVL(1) means independent VLAN learning. SVL means shared VLAN learning.

hh3cifEthernetFlowInterval.name: hh3cifEthernetFlowInterval
hh3cifEthernetFlowInterval.description: Set flow interval of the ethernet. The NMS should set value to integer which is a multiple of 5.

hh3cifEthernetIsolate.name: hh3cifEthernetIsolate
hh3cifEthernetIsolate.description: Isolate group means that all ports in the same isolate group can not send and receive packets each other. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight isolate groups, with the first octet specifying isolate groups 1 through 8, the second octet specifying isolate groups 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the leftmost bit is the first bit. the first bit represents the lowest numbered isolate group, and the last bit represents the highest numbered isolate group. one port can belong to more than one isolate group. Thus, each isolate group is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1', then that isolate group includes this port; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. for example, the first octet is '10000100' means that the port is included in the isolate group 1 and isolate group 6.

hh3cifVlanVPNTPID.name: hh3cifVlanVPNTPID
hh3cifVlanVPNTPID.description: Port based Vlan VPN TPID(Tag Protocol Indentifier), default value is 0x8100. Please refer to hh3cVlanVPNTPIDMode to get more information.

hh3cifIsolateGroupID.name: hh3cifIsolateGroupID
hh3cifIsolateGroupID.description: Isolate group identifier. Value zero means this interface does not belong to any isolate group.

hh3cifisUplinkPort.name: hh3cifisUplinkPort
hh3cifisUplinkPort.description: Ethernet uplink status, default value is 2.

hh3cifEthernetAutoSpeedMask.name: hh3cifEthernetAutoSpeedMask
hh3cifEthernetAutoSpeedMask.description: This object specifies which kinds of speed mode can be negotiated. Each bit corresponds to a kind of speed mode. If the value of a bit is '1', it means the corresponding speed mode is negotiable on the port. Otherwise the negotiation for that kind of speed mode is not supported on this port. If there are several negotiable speed modes, all bits for them are '1'. For example, if the speed mode 's10M' and 's1000M' can be negotiable, the value of this object is 0xA0.

hh3cifEthernetAutoSpeed.name: hh3cifEthernetAutoSpeed
hh3cifEthernetAutoSpeed.description: This object indicates which kinds of speed mode are negotiable on this port. Only when a bit of hh3cifEthernetAutoSpeedMask is '1', the corresponding bit of this object can be set to '1', indicating the corresponding speed mode is negotiable. For example, if the value of hh3cifEthernetAutoSpeedMask is 0xA0, which indicates speed mode 's10M' and 's1000M' are negotiable, the possible value of this object should be one of the four values (0x00, 0x20, 0x80 and 0xA0). If the value of hh3cifEthernetSpeed is not 'auto', the value of this object is insignificant and should be ignored. The value length of this object should be as long as that of hh3cifEthernetAutoSpeedMask.

hh3cIsolateGroupMax.name: hh3cIsolateGroupMax
hh3cIsolateGroupMax.description: Max isolate group that this device support, the value is zero means that the device does not support isolate group.

hh3cGlobalBroadcastMaxPps.name: hh3cGlobalBroadcastMaxPps
hh3cGlobalBroadcastMaxPps.description: The global max packets per second. When it is set, the value of BroadcastMaxPps in all ports will be changed to that setting.

hh3cGlobalBroadcastMaxRatio.name: hh3cGlobalBroadcastMaxRatio
hh3cGlobalBroadcastMaxRatio.description: The global max-ratio of broadcast from 0 to 100 percent. When it is set, the value of BroadcastMaxRatio in all ports will be changed to that setting.

hh3cVlanVPNTPIDMode.name: hh3cVlanVPNTPIDMode
hh3cVlanVPNTPIDMode.description: Vlan VPN TPID mode. The value 'port-based' means VLAN VPN TPID value would be set based on port via hh3cifVlanVPNTPID. In this situation, hh3cVlanVPNTPID is meaningless and always return 0x8100. The value 'global' means VLAN VPN TPID value should be set globally via hh3cVlanVPNTPID. In this situation, hh3cifVlanVPNTPID in hh3cethernetTable has the same value with hh3cVlanVPNTPID.

hh3cVlanVPNTPID.name: hh3cVlanVPNTPID
hh3cVlanVPNTPID.description: Global Vlan VPN TPID(Tag Protocol Indentifier), default value is 0x8100.

hh3cPortIsolateGroupIndex.name: hh3cPortIsolateGroupIndex
hh3cPortIsolateGroupIndex.description: Port isolate group identifier. The index of the hh3cPortIsolateGroupTable. The value ranges from 1 to the limit of isolate group quantity.

hh3cPortIsolateUplinkIfIndex.name: hh3cPortIsolateUplinkIfIndex
hh3cPortIsolateUplinkIfIndex.description: Index number of the uplink interface.

hh3cPortIsolateGroupRowStatus.name: hh3cPortIsolateGroupRowStatus
hh3cPortIsolateGroupRowStatus.description: Current operation status of the row.

hh3cPortIsolateGroupDescription.name: hh3cPortIsolateGroupDescription
hh3cPortIsolateGroupDescription.description: Port isolate group description, default value is zero-length string.

hh3cMaxMacLearnRange.name: hh3cMaxMacLearnRange
hh3cMaxMacLearnRange.description: The maximum number of MAC address that the port supports.
